[Method]
AddColumns
[Function]
dcl_Grid_AddColumns
[Desc]
This method adds columns to a Grid control. The width, justification, and optional image from the image list can or must be specified for each column.
\par \par The column justification is to be set using:
\par 0	Left (default)
\par 1	Center
\par 2	Right
\par \par \b Please Note:\b0 \par Due to limitations in the grid control, column 0 is always left justified and cannot be changed.
[Arguments]
<CONTROL>
\par\tab 
[Begin List]
[Begin List]
\par\tab sColText
[as String]
\par\tab \i{Optional} \i0 nJustification
[as Integer]
\par\tab \i{Optional} \i0 nColWidth
[as Integer]
\par\tab \i{Optional} \i0 nImageListIndex
[as Integer]
[End List]
\par\tab ...
[End List]


[Method]
AddRow
[Function]
dcl_Grid_AddRow
[Desc]
This method adds a new item to the end of a Grid control and will also fill in the cells in the entire row according to how many columns have been setup. Using this method the very first cell under the first column can be specified to display an image from the image list. Use \cf1 dcl_Grid_SetItemImage \cf0 to set the icons of any column cell.
\par \b Note:\b0 The style of the cell or column only governs the behavior of the cell and what happens when the user clicks on the cell.
\par \par \b \b For example \b0\b0if you set the style 33 - Linetype Cell, the current selection for the linetype must be correctly set in the \cf2 dcl_Grid_AddString \cf0 or \cf2 dcl_Grid_AddRow \cf0 functions. The item may not be changed to correctly display one of the listed items.
[Arguments Return] as Integer
<CONTROL>
\par\tab 
[Begin List]
\par\tab\i{Optional} \i0 nImageIndex ...
[as Integer]
\par\tab sText
[as String]
\par\tab\i{Optional} \i0 sColText1 sColText2 sColText3 ...
[as String]
[End List]


[Method]
AddString
[Function]
dcl_Grid_AddString
[Desc]
This method adds a new row to the end of a Grid control and fills in each of the cells using a single delimited string to specify the contents of each cell in the row. 
If the sDelimiter argument of this function is not specified, "\t" is assumed.

\par \par \b1 Please note: \b0 This function cannot specify image icons for the cells (however \cf2 dcl_Grid_SetItemImage \cf0 can be called afterward).
\par 
\par \b Also Note:\b0 The style of the cell or column only governs the behavior of the cell and what happens when the user clicks on the cell.
\par \par For example, if you specify a value for a cell with style 33 - Linetype Cell, the value you set must be an existing linetype.
[Arguments Return] as Integer
<CONTROL>
\par\tab sString
[as String]
\par\tab\i{Optional} \i0 sDelimiters
[as String]


[Method]
InsertString
[Function]
dcl_Grid_InsertString
[Desc]
This method inserts a new row at the specified position of a Grid control and fills in each of the cells using a single delimited string to specify the contents of each cell in the row. 
If the sDelimiter argument of this function is not specified, "\t" is assumed.

\par \par \b1 Please note: \b0 This function cannot specify image icons for the cells (however \cf2 dcl_Grid_SetItemImage \cf0 can be called afterward).
\par 
\par \b Also Note:\b0 The style of the cell or column only governs the behavior of the cell and what happens when the user clicks on the cell.
\par \par For example, if you specify a value for a cell with style 33 - Linetype Cell, the value you set must be an existing linetype.
[Arguments Return] as Integer
<CONTROL>
\par\tab nIndex
[as Integer]
\par\tab sString
[as String]
\par\tab \i{Optional} \i0 sDelimiters
[as String]


[Method]
GetColumnImage
[Function]
dcl_Grid_GetColumnImage
[Desc]
This method returns the image of a column header in a Grid control. 
[Arguments Return] as Integer
<CONTROL>
\par\tab nColumn
[as Integer]


[Method]
SetColumnImage
[Function]
dcl_Grid_SetColumnImage
[Desc]
This method sets the image of a column header in a Grid control. Set to -1 for no image.
[Arguments]
<CONTROL>
\par\tab nColumn
[as Integer]
\par\tab nImageIndex
[as Integer]


[Method]
GetColumnCount
[Function]
dcl_Grid_GetColumnCount
[Desc]
This method returns number of columns in a Grid control. 
[Arguments Return] as Integer
<CONTROL>


[Method]
GetRowCount
[Function]
dcl_Grid_GetRowCount
[Desc]
This method returns number of rows in a Grid control. 
[Arguments Return] as Integer
<CONTROL>


[Method]
InsertRow
[Function]
dcl_Grid_InsertRow
[Desc]
This method inserts a new item anywhere in a Grid control and will also fill in the cells in the entire row according to how many columns have been setup. Using this method the very first cell under the first column can be specified to display an image from the image list.  Use \cf2 dcl_Grid_SetItemImage \cf0 to set the icons of any column cell.
\par \b Note:\b0 The style of the cell or column only governs the behavior of the cell and what happens when the user clicks on the cell.
\par \par \b For example \b0if you set the style 33 - Linetype Cell, the current selection for the linetype must be correctly set in the \cf2 dcl_Grid_AddString \cf0 or \cf2 dcl_Grid_AddRow \cf0 functions. The item may not be changed to correctly display one of the listed items.
[Arguments Return] as Integer
<CONTROL>
\par\tab nInsertIndex
[as Integer]
\par\tab 
[Begin List]
\par\tab \i{Optional} \i0 nImageIndex
[as Integer]
\par\tab sText
[as String]
\par\tab\i{Optional} \i0 sColText1 sColText2 sColText3 ...
[as String]
[End List]


[Method]
InsertColumn
[Function]
dcl_Grid_InsertColumn
[Desc]
This method inserts a column in a Grid control. The width, justification, and optional image from the image list can or must be specified for each column.
\par \par The column justification is to be set using:
\par 0	Left (default)
\par 1	Center
\par 2	Right
\par \par \b Please Note:\b0 \par Due to limitations in the grid control, column 0 is always left justified and cannot be changed.
[Arguments]
<CONTROL>
\par\tab nInsertIndex
[as Integer]
[Begin List]
\par\tab sColText
[as String]
\par\tab \i{Optional} \i0 nJustification
[as Integer]
\par\tab \i{Optional} \i0 nColWidth
[as Integer]
\par\tab \i{Optional} \i0 nImageListIndex
[as Integer]
[End List]


[Method]
FillList
[Function]
dcl_Grid_FillList
[Desc]
This method will clear and fill a Grid control with multiple rows and will fill in the cells in each row according to how many columns have been previously setup. 
[Arguments]
<CONTROL>
[Begin List]
[Begin List]
sItem1Text
[as String]
\i{Optional} \i0 nImageListIndex1 
[as Integer]
sCol2Text
[as String]
\i{Optional} \i0 nImageListIndex2
[as Integer]
sCol3Text
[as String]
\i{Optional} \i0 nImageListIndex3
[as Integer]
...
[End List]
...
[End List]


[Method]
SetCurSel
[Function]
dcl_Grid_SetCurSel
[Desc]
This method will force a cell (or entire row if nColumn is omitted or set to -1) to be selected and will also scroll the Grid to ensure the item is displayed.
[Arguments]
<CONTROL>
\par\tab nRow
[as Integer]
\par\tab \i{Optional} \i0 nColumn
[as Integer]


[Method]
GetCurSel
[Function]
dcl_Grid_GetCurSel
[Desc]
This method will return the current row and column indexes of the currently selected cell. If the column index is -1 and the row index is 0 or above, this indicates the entire row is selected.
[Arguments]
<CONTROL>


[Method]
Clear
[Function]
dcl_Grid_Clear
[Desc]
This method will clear the Grid of all its items.
[Arguments]
<CONTROL>


[Method]
DeleteRow
[Function]
dcl_Grid_DeleteRow
[Desc]
This method will delete the specified row from the Grid control.
[Arguments]
<CONTROL>
\par\tab nRow
[as Integer]


[Method]
DeleteColumn
[Function]
dcl_Grid_DeleteColumn
[Desc]
This method will delete the specified column from the Grid control.
\b Note:\b0 A column can only be deleted if that column was not added using the properties wizard. A value of (-1 -1) means now cell has been selected.
[Arguments]
<CONTROL>
\par\tab nIndex
[as Integer]


[Method]
SetItemData
[Function]
dcl_Grid_SetItemData
[Desc]
This method will set the associated item data for the row. The item data will only accept integer values.
\par \b Note:\b0 The item data can only be set per individual row and not per cell.
[Arguments]
<CONTROL>
\par\tab nIndex
[as Integer]
\par\tab IntegerData
[as Integer]


[Method]
GetItemData
[Function]
dcl_Grid_GetItemData
[Desc]
This method will retrieve the associated item data for the indicated row.
[Arguments Return] as Integer
<CONTROL>
\par\tab nIndex
[as Integer]


